title: Another clue
author: VD
content_html:
From the Star Tribune: Democratic presidential candidate John Kerry swooped into the Twin Cities Monday evening, drew more than 3,500 people to fundraisers at the Minneapolis Convention Center and picked up nearly $1 million for his campaign and the national Democratic Party.

This illustrates another problem for Jean-Francois. It can’t be a good sign when he raises less than half as much as George Delano did in their respective single-day sweeps through one of the most left-liberal states in the country.
